history.content: 170 is going to help you get an internship more than any other class. I personally think 186 and 161 are a waste of time. 186 is a worse version of 162 IMO, and 161 felt like a trivia class. If you're willing to take 2 problem set based classes, I would encourage 170 and 127 but it'll be a good amount of work.

children.subject: Because they won't help you machine learn
In all seriousness though take it if you're interested.
Could you expand on why you think 186 and 161 are waste of time?

history.content:
Hi! I was originally going to take cs170, cs161, and cs186 next semester, but I realize I do want to take more classes related to AI/ML so I wanted to take ee127 or ee126 next semester. Since ee127 and cs186 overlap, my options are:

1)cs170, cs161, cs186 (my original plan)

2)cs170, cs161, ee127 

3)cs170, cs186, ee126

I've heard cs186 is pretty good for internships which is why I would like to take it, but cs161 sounds more interesting to me. I don't really have preference about ee127 or ee126, but my main concern is I'm not sure how relevant ee126/7 are to my internship search rather than more concrete courses like 161 and 186. 

If anyone has any advice about these courses or what order I should take them in(or if there is a better combination I haven't considered), that would be greatly appreciated!
history.subject: CS186 + EE126 or CS161 + EE127
